column8: Thank you, some is us need reminders to sit a little longer in that darkness
So much to learn in the things that we don’t see.

I based my final year uni artwork around dark matter, and the idea of mapping out or visualising phenomena that are simply beyond the perception of human eyes, because of scale or the confines of the visible light spectrum. I spent a whole, fascinating year reading about dark matter for that and it still blows my mind that visible, detectable matter makes up such a tiny fraction of the known universe 😍
Pure poetry 🦋 thank you for sharing 💖
I love how this piece is a mix of poetry, education, and connections to current events. Very touching and thought provoking!
There’s those who get frustrated by the unknown... and then those of us who are excited by the possibilities of it and the thrill of discovery... in science and in daily life
Good post... I think you’ll enjoy Jorge Cham’s “We have no idea”
